'''Functional zoning''' or functional city [[zoning]] is a method used for dividing [[land use]] by its function.<ref name="Dubrova, Podlipskiy,Kurilenko, Siabato">{{Cite web|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/270002179_Functional_city_zoning_Environmental_assessment_of_eco-geological_substance_migration_flows|title=Functional city zoning. Environmental assessment of eco-geological substance migration flows (PDF Download Available)|last=Dubrova|first=Stanislav|last2=Podlipskiy|first2=Ivan|date=|website=ResearchGate|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-05-21|last3=Kurilenko|first3=Vitaliy|last4=Siabato|first4=Willington}}</ref> Typically, land use is divided in two ways, by its function and by its physical characteristics.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Planning and Community Development|last=Tyler|first=Norman|publisher=W.W. Norton & Company Inc.|year=2011|isbn=978-0-393-73292-4|location=New York, NY|pages=188}}</ref> An example of functional zoning would be an area that has designated zones based on a function such as an industrial zone, a recreational zone and a residential zone.<ref name="Dubrova, Podlipskiy,Kurilenko, Siabato" /> An example of an area zoned by its physical characteristics is defined in terms of characteristics like development density, minimum lot size, and building coverage, placement and height.<ref name="Dubrova, Podlipskiy,Kurilenko, Siabato"/>

Functional zoning tends to create or increase [[Automobile dependency|car dependency]], while [[Mixed-use development|mixed-use]] zoning tends to enable walking, making it more [[Sustainability|sustainable]].<ref>{{Cite book|title=Public places urban spaces: the dimensions of urban design|last=Carmona|first=Mathew|publisher=Routledge|year=2010|isbn=9781856178273|edition=2nd|location=London|pages=222}}</ref> It has been criticized for causing the squandering of land, energy, and time.<ref>{{Cite book|title=The architecture of community|last=Krier|first=Léon|publisher=Island Press|year=2009|isbn=9781597265782|location=Washington|pages=105}}</ref>

