{{Europe-sci-mag-stub}}

{{LHC}} '''MoEDAL''' ('''Monopole and Exotics Detector at the LHC''') is a [[particle physics]] experiment at the [[Large Hadron Collider]] (LHC).
==Experiment== MoEDAL shares the cavern at Point 8 with [[LHCb]], and its prime goal is to directly search for the [[magnetic monopole]] (MM)<ref>{{cite arxiv |last1=Giacomelli |first1=G. |last2=Sioli |first2=M. |year=2002 |title=Astroparticle Physics |eprint=hep-ex/0211035}}</ref><ref>{{cite arxiv |last1=Giacomelli |first1=G. |last2=Patrizii |first2=L. |year=2001 |title=Magnetic Monopoles |eprint=hep-ex/0112009}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Kalbfleisch |first1=G. R. |last2=Milton |first2=K. A. |last3=Strauss |first3=M. G. |last4=Gamberg |first4=L. |last5=Smith |first5=E. H. |last6=Luo |first6=W. |year=2000 |title=Improved Experimental Limits on the Production of Magnetic Monopoles |journal=[[Physical Review Letters]] |volume=85 |issue=25 |pages=5292–5295 |arxiv=hep-ex/0005005 |bibcode=2000PhRvL..85.5292K |doi=10.1103/PhysRevLett.85.5292 |pmid=11135979}}</ref><ref>{{cite arxiv |last1=Milton |first1=K. A. |last2=Kalbfleisch |first2=G. R. |last3=Strauss |first3=M. G. |last4=Gamberg |first4=L. |last5=Luo |first5=W. |last6=Smith |first6=E. H. |year=2000 |title=New Limits on the Production of Magnetic Monopoles at Fermilab |eprint=hep-ex/0009003}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal |last1=Abbott |first1=B. |display-authors=etal. |collaboration=D0 Collaboration |year=1998 |title=Search for Heavy Pointlike Dirac Monopoles |journal=[[Physical Review Letters]] |volume=81|issue=3|pages=524–529 |arxiv=hep-ex/9803023 |bibcode=1998PhRvL..81..524A |doi=10.1103/PhysRevLett.81.524}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last=Giacomelli |first=G. |year=1984 |title=Magnetic monopoles |journal=[[Rivista del Nuovo Cimento]] |volume=7 |issue=12 |pages=1–111 |bibcode=1984NCimR...7l...1G |doi=10.1007/BF02724347|arxiv=hep-ex/0002032 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last=Acciarri |first=M. |collaboration=L3 Collaboration |display-authors=etal. |year=1995 |title=Search for anomalous Z → γγγ events at LEP |journal=[[Physics Letters B]] |volume=345 |issue=4|pages=609–616 |bibcode=1995PhLB..345..609A|doi=10.1016/0370-2693(95)01612-T|url=http://cds.cern.ch/record/273745 |type=Submitted manuscript }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal |last1=Gamberg |first1=L. |last2=Kalbfleisch |first2=G. R. |last3=Milton |first3=K. A. |year=2000 |title=Direct and Indirect Searches for Low-Mass Magnetic Monopoles |journal=[[Foundations of Physics]] |volume=30 |issue= 4|pages=543–565 |arxiv=hep-ph/9906526 |bibcode=1999hep.ph....6526G |doi=10.1023/a:1003668812097}}</ref> or [[dyon]] and other highly ionizing [[stable massive particle]]s (SMPs) and pseudo-stable massive particles. To detect these particles, the project uses [[Solid-state nuclear track detector|nuclear track detectors]] (NTDs), which suffer characteristic damage due to highly ionizing particles. As MMs and SMPs are highly ionizing, NTDs are perfectly suited for the purpose of detection.
It is an international research collaboration whose spokesperson is the [[University of Alberta]]'s James Pinfold. It is the seventh experiment at the LHC, was approved and sanctioned by the [[CERN]] research board on May 2010, and started its first test deployment in January 2011.<ref>{{cite web |last=Pinfold |first=J. |date=5 May 2010 |title=MoEDAL becomes the LHC's magnificent seventh |url=http://cerncourier.com/cws/article/cern/42329 |work=[[CERN Courrier]] |accessdate=2016-07-14}}</ref>
In 2012 MoEDAL accuracy surpassed accuracy of similar experiments. A new detector was installed in 2015,<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Acharya |first1=B. |display-authors=etal. |collaboration=MoEDAL Collaboration |year=2016 |title=Search for magnetic monopoles with the MoEDAL prototype trapping detector in 8 TeV proton-proton collisions at the LHC |arxiv=1604.06645 |doi=10.1007/JHEP08(2016)067 |volume=2016 |issue=8 |pages=67 |journal=Journal of High Energy Physics|bibcode=2016JHEP...08..067A }}</ref> but as of 2017 it also did not find any magnetic monopoles, setting new limits on their production cross section.<ref>{{Cite journal | doi=10.1103/PhysRevLett.118.061801 |doi-access=free| pmid=28234515|title = Search for Magnetic Monopoles with the MoEDAL Forward Trapping Detector in 13&nbsp;TeV Proton-Proton Collisions at the LHC| journal=Physical Review Letters| volume=118| issue=6| pages=061801|year = 2017|last1 = Acharya |first1 = B. |collaboration=MoEDAL Collaboration | displayauthors=etal}}</ref>
