{{Taxobox | name = Mycobacterium phage L5 | image_caption = | image = | virus_group = i | ordo = ''[[Caudovirales]]'' | familia = ''[[Siphoviridae]]'' | genus = ''[[L5likevirus]]'' | species = '''''Mycobacterium phage L5''''' }}
'''''Mycobacterium phage L5''''' is a [[bacteriophage]] known to infect bacterial species of the genus ''[[Mycobacterium]]''.<ref>{{cite journal|last=Hatfull|first=Graham F.|author2=Sarkis, Gary J.|title=DNA sequence, structure and gene expression of mycobacteriophage L5: a phage system for mycobacterial genetics|journal=Molecular Microbiology|date=1 February 1993|volume=7|issue=3|pages=395–405|doi=10.1111/j.1365-2958.1993.tb01131.x|pmid=8459766}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last=Lee|first=M. H.|author2=Pascopella, L. |author3=Jacobs, W. R. |author4= Hatfull, G. F. |title=Site-specific integration of mycobacteriophage L5: integration-proficient vectors for Mycobacterium smegmatis, Mycobacterium tuberculosis, and bacille Calmette-Guerin.|journal=Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences|date=15 April 1991|volume=88|issue=8|pages=3111–3115|doi=10.1073/pnas.88.8.3111|pmc=51395}}</ref>
